SEVEN people died on the spot on Sunday after a car crashed into a cart at Lugala village, in Chamwino District, Dodoma region. The cart, pulled by two cows, was carrying 12 passengers to Lugala Mountain in the early hours to collect soil for pottery. They were hit from behind by the vehicle, a Toyota Land Cruiser with registration number STL 9534, belonging to the Katavi Regional water department, which was heading to Mtera from Dodoma, driven by Paschal Paulo (29). Dodoma Regional Police Commander, Assistant Commissioner of Police (ACP) Martin Otieno said the incident occurred on Sunday at 5am at the village which is located in Chamwino District on the Iringa-Dodoma highway. "The vehicle was at high speed and the driver could not see the cart and had hit it from behind before it overturned," he said over the phone. Otieno said the seven casualties were passengers of the cart, while the other five passengers escaped with injuries.  The two cows also died on the spot. RPC Otieno said the driver of the vehicle is being held for interrogation and further legal measures. ACP Otieno added the survivors were rushed to Dodoma Regional Referral Hospital for treatment. According to Mnzase Ward councillor John Mika, it is a daily routine for villagers to go to the mountain to collect soil. 